<div id="review_1357591539" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1357591539" />
    <a title="Patty" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1335650-patty"><img alt="Patty" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442602899p2/1335650.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1357591539?book_show_action=true">Aug 07, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Patty" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Patty" href="/user/show/1335650-patty">Patty</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1335650-patty?shelf=memoir">memoir</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1357591539" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2503130459528955652">As soon as I opened this book to the first page, I was hooked. The modern story of a search for love as told by the main character, Morgan Stanfield is hauntingly compelling. Author Frank Scozzari writes in such a way that draws you in, finds you cheering for his dream, but at the same time, we want to shout at him to stop. We feel his hope, his yearning, and we become invested in the emotion that compels him forward. A trip to Russia against his friend’s advice finds him in a hopeless tangle of</span>
  <span id="freeText2503130459528955652" style="display:none">As soon as I opened this book to the first page, I was hooked. The modern story of a search for love as told by the main character, Morgan Stanfield is hauntingly compelling. Author Frank Scozzari writes in such a way that draws you in, finds you cheering for his dream, but at the same time, we want to shout at him to stop. We feel his hope, his yearning, and we become invested in the emotion that compels him forward. A trip to Russia against his friend’s advice finds him in a hopeless tangle of misfortunes. The care in which he crafts the characters is wonderful. The pace of the story keeps you turning the pages. The emotion wrenches your heart. This author is definitely one I will follow.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2503130459528955652" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

