  <span id="freeText2576350738295491087" style="display:none">This is the story of hopeless romantic, Morgan Stanfield, and his search for true love in Russia. I love the way Frank Scozzari brought the characters together. From Morgan's weekly pub friends in Santa Barbara CA to the Russian doorman in St. Petersburg. The characters are authentic and involving. While Morgan's trip to Russia turns into a comedy of errors and he leaves with a deep sense of loss, I was left with a feeling of hope. His friend Kim, back in Santa Barbara, is rooting for him to find love and not sex. I say he should explore his relationship with her. Sounds like she is as romantically inclined as he is. It would be fun for him to travel halfway around the world to find love exactly 2 centimeters away from him!</span>
