<div id="review_1397715481" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1397715481" />
    <a title="Tony Piazza" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6768648-tony-piazza"><img alt="Tony Piazza" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1508950429p2/6768648.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1397715481?book_show_action=true">Sep 21, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tony Piazza" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tony Piazza" href="/user/show/6768648-tony-piazza">Tony Piazza</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6768648-tony-piazza?shelf=from-afar-by-frank-scozzari">from-afar-by-frank-scozzari</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6768648-tony-piazza?shelf=this-novel-is-a-gem">this-novel-is-a-gem</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1397715481" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10470882476668894864">I enjoyed &quot;From Afar: A Memoir.&quot; In fact, I enjoyed it so much that I wasn&apos;t able to put it down. It was a page turner from beginning to end. Mr. Scozzari is an extremely talented writer- I&apos;ll even go so far as to say, gifted, and I predict we&apos;ll be hearing more about him and his stories in the days to come. &quot;From Afar: A Memoir&quot; is an entertaining story about a young man looking for love in all the wrong places. It&apos;s at times humorous, philosophical, and thoughtful. You can&apos;t help getting caugh</span>
  <span id="freeText10470882476668894864" style="display:none">I enjoyed "From Afar: A Memoir." In fact, I enjoyed it so much that I wasn't able to put it down. It was a page turner from beginning to end. Mr. Scozzari is an extremely talented writer- I'll even go so far as to say, gifted, and I predict we'll be hearing more about him and his stories in the days to come. "From Afar: A Memoir" is an entertaining story about a young man looking for love in all the wrong places. It's at times humorous, philosophical, and thoughtful. You can't help getting caught up in it. It's a tale of reality verses romanticism. What could be, in contrast to what life actually has in story. It's a commentary on our times, and especially our views on love. But, it's also something else. A great adventure where Mr. Scozzari takes his readers into Russia, and introduces the people, the customs, cultures, history, and sights. I've never been to Russia, but his prose certainly left me feeling like I've been there. Along the way he introduces the readers to many interesting characters- some nice, some not so nice. "From Afar: A Memoir" is a story that will not fade from my conscience. In many instances I felt a bond to the protagonist. There's a romantic in us all, and Mr. Scozzari brought it out of this reader. I was rooting all the way for his protagonist's success! I highly recommend this book. It's a gem that shouldn't be missed. A jewel worthy of Catherine the Great herself.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10470882476668894864" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


