      <div class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/work/quotes/44690948-from-afar">Quotes from From Afar</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;She said there was no such thing as the perfect match. She claimed it was a grand fallacy. There was no such thing as a ‘soulmate.’ She said that. She said many perfectly content couples were ruined by the concept; that too many couples, ninety percent of them perfect for one another, were ruined because the remaining ten percent was proof, to one or the other, that their true ‘soulmate’ lay elsewhere, and therefore the relationship ended.&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/quotes/9349429-she-said-there-was-no-such-thing-as-the-perfect">1 likes</a>
            </nobr>
            <div class="clear"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;You have but one life to live; and not many chances to get the love thing right. In fact, some people never get it right, and grow old living together but living separate, miserable lives. If you believe in love, you must fight for it. You must hold out for it. You must not give up. You must remain hopelessly romantically alone until your true love is found. You must sacrifice and suffer in loneliness, until one day it finds you.&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/quotes/9349437-you-have-but-one-life-to-live-and-not-many">0 likes</a>
            </nobr>
